\section intro Introduction

Juicer is a Weighted Finite State Transducer (WFST) based decoder for
Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR).  It has been developed as a
collaboration between Idiap and the universities of Sheffield and
Edinburgh under the <a href="http://www.amiproject.org/">AMI and
AMIDA</a> projects.

Juicer has been successfully used in the AMI consortium entries in
the recent NIST RT evaluations.  It is used as a real-time
demonstration engine in AMIDA, and increasingly as the main research
engine in other projects.

